Description: SaaS business tool for collecting and analyzing customer satisfaction data using QR-enabled smileys to gather feedback.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: AirVote® is a business tool for collecting and analyzing customer satisfaction data. The primary goal of the tool is to flag to a business team service problem areas and give an opportunity to correct before they appear in social media as a negative review. This self-service platform features an easy and scalable way to acquire data: business owners or delegates register and claim their business and create questions they want to ask.  The system automatically generates a unique set of QR smileys.  Questions are printed as stickers or posters and placed in various locations of customer traffic.  By scanning a respective QR smiley customers anonymously vote with one click and an optional comment.  Happy customers are offered a direct link to a social channel of business’ choice to leave a formal review.  Customer feedback data is instantly available to the business owner via a central dashboard.  Data can be viewed by time, question, business site, or placement location. Configurable real-time alerts send instant notifications to the business about unhappy votes and any associated comments. The tiered pricing model is based on usage.  Independently of the tier, any usage below 50 votes per month is free.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Data and Analytics, Hardware, Software

Description: WebAct is an advanced website builder in that helps you convert traffic by the visitor and allows you to build your website by device.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Denver Area, Western US
Full Description: WebAct is based in Denver, Colorado, and is one of the fastest growing web companies in Colorado. At WebAct, we know that not all websites are created equal, that is why we build websites specifically to convert the traffic into new customers. WebAct is also a certified partner of Google, Bing, and Facebook for all of your search solution and online marketing needs. Our mission is to be a complete website and search solution for our customers. We customize our solutions for our clients so they can run their business and leave their web presence to us. WebAct was created in 2012 to help small to medium size business grow online without all of the high costs associated with web design and online marketing. Our company focused on working with only new business or home based businesses, however what we came to realize was that even large companies and fortune 5000 companies were spending too much without getting their return on investment. We have partnered with technology, marketing, and web companies to deliver a platform that will help all businesses convert their web traffic into sales. Our headquarters are in Denver, Colorado, but our business is worldwide. When we build your website you get more than just a plain ol' desktop site. Each site we build is multi-device optimized so your customers will always get the best experience, no matter which device they use. Since our sites are built by the device, we can include certain elements on the mobile version that you wouldn't want on the desktop version, like click-to-call and GPS mapping for example. Did you know that 60% of all internet traffic is on mobile devices? And that websites that are not mobile optimized are omitted from mobile searches on Google? 60% of all internet traffic is a lot to miss out on! This is why having just a desktop site does not cut it anymore and why your company needs a multi-device optimized website.
